<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 3200, 4100, 4200, 4300, 4400, 7300, 7400, 7500, 7600, 8500, 8600
        Models Built After 05/19/2003 - HOOD, GRILLE, FENDERS AND BUMPER - 4100, 4200, 4300, 4400 - REMOVE AND INSTALL -
        SPLASH PANELS
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="3">
        <title>SPLASH PANELS</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Splash Panel- Removal</title>
            <para>The splash panels (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0900318">Figure 18</hotlnk>) on the 41/42/43/4400 series minimize splash and mud,
                protecting vital engine systems from corrosion and malfunction.
            </para>
            <para>
                <title>Splash Panel Removal: Passenger Side</title>
            </para>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0900319">Figure 19</hotlnk>
                for Items in parentheses.
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tilt the hood assembly forward and locate the attachment bolts (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0900319">Item 6</hotlnk>) at the forward lower section of the splash guard mounting
                    bracket (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0900319">Item 7</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Locate the rear splash panel mounting bracket (passenger side shown) (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0900319">Item 2</hotlnk>). Remove the mounting bolts (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0900319">Items 1 and 3</hotlnk>) from the mounting bracket (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0900319">Item 2</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the splash panel.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0900318" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/G0900318.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="312px"
                         scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Figure 18. Splash Panel -Passenger Side Shown</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. SPLASH PANEL - PASSENGER SIDE</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. LOWER FENDER SECTION</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. HEADLIGHT HOUSING</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. BUMPER</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. HEADLIGHT AND CLEARANCE LIGHT HARNESS</callout1>
                    <callout1>6. CHASSIS FRAME</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <para>
                <title>Splash Panel Removal - Drivers Side</title>
            </para>
            <seqlist style="arabic">
                <item>
                    <para>With the hood tilted locate the driver side 2 forward mounting bolts (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f0900320">Item 2, Figure 20</hotlnk>) attaching the splash panel to the front
                        hood assembly.
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Remove the bolts and lock washers.</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Remove the 2 rear splash panel mounting bolts and lock washers located along the upper edge of
                        the splash panel.
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Remove the splash panel assembly.</para>
                </item>
            </seqlist>
            <figure id="f0900319" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/G0900319.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="312px"
                         scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Figure 19. Splash Panel Removal (Passenger Side Shown)</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. SPLASH PANEL MOUNTING BOLTS</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. SPLASH PANEL MOUNTING BRACKET</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. SPLASH PANEL MOUNTING BOLTS</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. FRAME RAIL SPLASH PANEL BRACKET MOUNTING POINTS, REAR</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. FRAME RAIL SPLASH PANEL BRACKET MOUNTING POINTS, FRONT</callout1>
                    <callout1>6. MOUNTING BOLTS</callout1>
                    <callout1>7. FRONT SPLASH PANEL MOUNTING BRACKET</callout1>
                    <callout1>8. HOOD</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Splash Panel - Install</title>
            <para>Beginning on the passenger side:</para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Align the splash panel mounting holes with the mounting brackets and insert the mounting
                    bolts and lock washers.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Hand tighten only.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Align the rear mounting holes with the mounting bracket assemblies.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Insert the mounting bolts and lock washers.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten the splash panel mounting bolts.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0900320" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/G0900320.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                         scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 20. Splash Panel Install (Drivers Side Shown)</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. HOOD TILTED UPPER DRIVERS SIDE SECTION</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. TWO UPPER SPLASH SHIELD MOUNTING BOLTS</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. SPLASH PANEL</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position the hood/fender splash panel on the inner fender of the hood/fender assembly (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0900320">Item 2, Figure 20</hotlnk>). Install the 2 forward mounting bolts and lock
                    washer to the hood/fender assembly.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position the 2 rear splash panel mounting holes in place on the hood and install the
                    mounting bolts and lock washers, securing it to the hood assembly.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten the bolts to the required torque.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Close hood and lock hood latches.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
